$ gcc -fverbose-asm

If compiling with → development/languages/C-C-plus-plus/GCC/options/S_uppercase[`-S`] to produce → development/languages/C-C-plus-plus/GCC/as[assembly output], adding the `-fverbose-asm` flag
adds extra inline-commentary to the produced file to make it more readable.

{ prog.c

  A simple program:
  gh|about-gcc|/options/f/verbose-asm/prog.c||

}
{ Makefile

  This is the → development/make/index[makefile] that creates `proc.s` with additional comments:
  gh|about-gcc|/options/f/verbose-asm/Makefile||

}

sa:
  → development/languages/C-C-plus-plus/GCC/options
